messages.messageBody:
"And nervous...we have 10 days to move and I haven't packed a thing, save
three boxes of books. AAAAHHH!"

Hey, you did the important stuff first...cool.
You can do it!! I packed 90% of our 3200 sf house by myself, with an 8month old baby in tow when we moved down to FL five years ago. UGH!
Wouldn't want to do it again, but we survived.

Just breathe deep and chant to yourself a lot. :)

AND, when you get time, email me with your new addy and I'll mail the pics of the ocean/ship themed stuff.

Ren

messages.msgSnippet: We got a house!  I m SO happy and excited!!! And nervous...we have 10 days to move and I haven t packed a thing, save three boxes of books.  AAAAHHH! Add that
messages.messageBody:
We got a house! I'm SO happy and excited!!!

And nervous...we have 10 days to move and I haven't packed a thing, save
three boxes of books. AAAAHHH!

Add that to the fact that I'm packing and moving alone...my husband
conveniently doesn't get home until the day AFTER we have to be out of this
house...and I'm a nervous wreck!

At least I'm a nervous wreck with a house...could be worse!

Just had to share something good since I've been feeling so sorry for myself
as of late. :)

Jennifer
